# Walkthrough — Bug Fix + User Manual

## 1. Bug Fix: All chapters skipped (SKIP)

**Root cause**: [_create_and_submit_job](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#2089-2143) in [rewrite_style_tab.py](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py) created job dicts without caching word count values. Worker threads defaulted to [(0, 0)](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1181-1184) → [build_word_count_rule(0, 0)](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#49-59) returned `"SKIP"` for ALL chapter sections.

**Fix**: Added 7 cached values to the job dict at creation time:

```diff:rewrite_style_tab.py
"""
rewrite_style_tab.py — UI tab for Style-Guide based Rewrite pipeline.
Two modes: Top/List Review (review pipeline) and Narrative (narrative pipeline),
each using a style guide JSON with pipeline-specific frameworks.
